Items.description: Risotto is a northern Italian rice dish cooked with broth until it reaches a creamy consistency. The broth can be derived from meat, fish, or vegetables. Many types of risotto contain butter, onion, white wine, and parmesan cheese. It is one of the most common ways of cooking rice in Italy.

steps.instruction: Dice the onions and garlic into small pieces
Start frying the onions and  garlic in a generous amount of olive oil until they are translucent and soft. Keep the onions stirring and do not let them stick or burn
Boil a kettle of water. This water is going to become stock
Dissolve 2 stock cubes in a mug of the boiled water. Don't worry if the stock cubes don't fully dissolve at this point. You will be refilling this mug a few times
Pour the rice into the saucepan and really coat the grains in the excess olive oil. Coating the grains will ensure that they keep a good texture when the stock gets added
Add one mug of the stock liquid to the pan. Bring the pan upto the boil then turn the temperature down to a low heat
After five minutes as the water begins to be absorbed add another mug of boiling water. Make sure you get all the stock cube out of the mug
Add water for the third time. Make sure the water is boiling as it is added
Add water for the fourth time. This will be the last time. The rice should be looking soft and fluffy
Stir in some frozen peas. This adds some colour and a different texture. They only need to be in the pan for a sort time before serving
Serve with a drizzle of olive oil and a sprig of parsley. Serving suggestion: Goes really nicely with a glass of white wine

Items.description: An egg dish that blends the whites and yolks of eggs with milk and seasonings to be cooked in an open pan. When making Scrambled Eggs, heat the pan prior to cooking the eggs to assist in sealing the pan and keeping the eggs from sticking to the pan. When the top part of the pan sidewall is warm to the touch then the pan has been sufficiently heated. Spray or heat cooking oil so that it lightly coats the bottom of the pan and then pour the egg mixture into the pan

steps.instruction: Crack all the eggs into a medium sized bowl
steps.detail: Season the eggs with salt and pepper

steps.instruction: Scramble the eggs with a fork
steps.detail: The more you whisk the lighter the eggs will be

steps.instruction: Melt the butter in a saucepan on a medium heat
steps.detail: Choose the widest flattest pan you have to cook the eggs more evenly

steps.instruction: Add the eggs slowly and keep stirring with a wooden spoon
steps.detail: Do not let the eggs stick. Keep them moving and turn them down to a lower heat to cook them more slowly
Once the milk has all evaporated and absorbed, it ready to serve up

steps.instruction: Serve with a drizzle of olive oil
steps.detail: Serving suggestion: Goes really nicely on hot buttered toast and a mug of tea
